<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="166" pageId="3" pageNumber="165" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,1658,2007]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1436,151,320]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="166" pageId="3" pageNumber="165">
It is currently unclear whether 
<taxonomicName box="[554,672,1839,1862]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Macroscelesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japona">
<emphasis box="[554,672,1839,1862]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="165">M. japona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs on the East Asian mainland. So far only one specimen has been recorded from 
<collectingCountry box="[379,446,1874,1899]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="165">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Kallies" box="[461,610,1874,1899]" pageId="3" pageNumber="165" refString="Kallies, A. (2007) A revision of the clearwing moth species described by Zukowsky from China with additional notes on Sesiidae species from the Mell collection (Sesiidae). Nota lepidopterologica, 30 (2), 387 - 396." type="journal article" year="2007">Kallies 2007</bibRefCitation>
). However, neither the precise collecting locality nor its identity could be fully established. Based on 
<bibRefCitation author="Zukowsky" box="[464,665,1910,1935]" pageId="3" pageNumber="165" refString="Zukowsky, B. (1929) Beitrage zur Fauna sinica (VIII). Die sudchinesischen Aegeriiden der Sammlung Mell. Internationale Entomologische Zeitschrift, 23 (3), 33 - 37." type="journal article" year="1929">Zukowsky (1929)</bibRefCitation>
(as 
<taxonomicName authority="Bartel, 1912" authorityName="Bartel" authorityYear="1912" box="[713,1063,1910,1935]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Melittia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eurytion">
<emphasis box="[713,916,1911,1934]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="165">M. eurytion sensu</emphasis>
Bartel, 1912
</taxonomicName>
[= 
<taxonomicName authority="Hampson, 1919" authorityName="Hampson" authorityYear="1919" box="[1104,1373,1911,1935]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Macroscelesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japona">
<emphasis box="[1104,1182,1911,1934]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="165">japona</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hampson" box="[1189,1373,1911,1935]" pageId="3" pageNumber="165" refString="Hampson, G. F. (1919) A classification of the Aegeriadae [sic] of the Oriental and Ethiopian Regions. Novitates Zoologicae, 26 (1), 46 - 119." type="journal article" year="1919">Hampson, 1919</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
]), the specimen was collected on the 
<date box="[503,609,1946,1971]" pageId="3" pageNumber="165" value="1917-06-09">
9.vi. 
<quantity box="[548,609,1946,1971]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.86918" pageId="3" pageNumber="165" unit="in" value="1917.0">1917</quantity>
</date>
in “Gao fung” (South 
<collectingCountry box="[868,940,1946,1971]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="165">China</collectingCountry>
). It was assigned to 
<taxonomicName box="[1170,1286,1947,1970]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Macroscelesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="165" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japona">
<emphasis box="[1170,1286,1947,1970]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="165">M. japona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on the external appearance (
<bibRefCitation author="Kallies" box="[388,537,1982,2007]" pageId="3" pageNumber="165" refString="Kallies, A. (2007) A revision of the clearwing moth species described by Zukowsky from China with additional notes on Sesiidae species from the Mell collection (Sesiidae). Nota lepidopterologica, 30 (2), 387 - 396." type="journal article" year="2007">Kallies 2007</bibRefCitation>
). However, the genitalia morphology in this Chinese specimen differs somewhat from that of typical Japanese specimens, leaving open the possibility that it may represent another species of the 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Macroscelesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japona">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="166">M. japona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group. Differences include the shape of the sclerotized area around the ostium, in particular its significantly longer plate-like distal extension (
<figureCitation box="[543,625,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 11, 12" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1715,1738]" captionTargetBox="[253,1321,180,1684]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[233,1350,169,1692]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 11, 12. Female genitalia of Melittiini from China. 11. Macroscelesia japona (Gen. prep. AK 184, MNHB). 12. Macroscelesia vietnamica (Gen. Prep. AK 770, SCAU)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/192926/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="166">Fig. 11</figureCitation>
) and the longer ductus bursae (cf. 
<bibRefCitation author="Arita" box="[1033,1230,223,248]" pageId="4" pageNumber="166" refString="Arita, Y., Kimura, M., Yata, N. &amp; Nagase, M. (2016) Vicariance in the Macroscelesia japona species - group (Lepidoptera, Sesiidae) in the Ryukyus, Japan. Tinea, 23 (4), 184 - 198." type="journal article" year="2016">
Arita 
<emphasis box="[1100,1151,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="166">et al</emphasis>
. 2016
</bibRefCitation>
). Therefore, more material is needed to firmly establish the identity of the mainland populations of 
<taxonomicName box="[1084,1202,261,284]" class="Insecta" family="Sesiidae" genus="Macroscelesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="japona">
<emphasis box="[1084,1202,261,284]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="166">M. japona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This would also be critical for the material from 
<collectingCountry box="[477,548,296,319]" name="South Korea" pageId="4" pageNumber="166">Korea</collectingCountry>
, which has not been examined in detail (Arita 
<emphasis box="[1069,1117,296,320]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="166">et al</emphasis>
. 2004).
</paragraph>
